<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Frequently Asked Questions - Running Training Plan</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Get answers to frequently asked questions about Running Training Plan. Learn about pricing, features, compatibility, and more.">
    
    <!-- JSON-LD Schema for FAQPage -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "1. How much does the AI running training plan generator cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Four pricing tiers: Free (1 plan at a time, basic schedules), Premium ($7.99/month, unlimited plans, GPS integration), Pro ($14.99/month, AI form analysis, injury prevention), Elite ($29.99/month, 1-on-1 coach access, race day strategy). Students save 50% with .edu email verification. Annual billing saves 30%. 14-day free trial for all paid plans includes full feature access."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "2. How does the AI generate personalized training plans?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The AI analyzes: current fitness level (VO2 max estimate from recent runs), goal race/distance, target finish time, available training days/week, injury history, age, weight, and preferences (trail vs. road, morning vs. evening). It uses machine learning models trained on 100,000+ successful training cycles. Plans auto-adjust weekly based on performance data. Users report 23% faster improvement vs. static plans."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "3. Which running apps and devices does it sync with?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Integrations include Garmin, Strava, Apple Health, Nike Run Club, Adidas Running, Coros, Polar, and Suunto. Data synced: distance, pace, heart rate, elevation, cadence, and perceived exertion. Two-way sync enables the AI to adjust future workouts based on completed run performance. API access (Elite plan) enables custom integrations. Sync latency: <30 seconds for Premium+."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "4. Can the AI adapt my plan if I miss workouts or get injured?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, the AI dynamically reschedules missed workouts and adjusts intensity based on fatigue signals (elevated resting heart rate, decreased HRV, sleep quality). Injury prevention mode reduces impact workouts by 50% and substitutes low-impact cross-training when risk factors detected. Users report 67% fewer injuries vs. static plans. Recovery week auto-insertion occurs when cumulative fatigue score exceeds threshold."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "5. Does it support race-specific training (marathon, ultramarathon, trail)?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, plan types include: 5K, 10K, Half Marathon, Marathon, Ultramarathon (50K-100M), Trail races, and custom distances. Each includes race-specific workouts: tempo runs, interval sessions, long runs with nutrition timing, tapering strategies, and race week carb-loading guides. Trail plans factor in elevation gain/loss and technical terrain simulation. Ultramarathon plans include back-to-back long run weekends."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "6. How accurate are the pace and time predictions?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Pace predictions achieve ±3% accuracy based on validation against 5,000 race results. The AI refines predictions weekly as it learns your fitness trajectory. Factors considered: recent race results, training load trends, heart rate zones, and environmental conditions (heat, humidity, altitude). Users receive updated target paces every Monday. Prediction confidence intervals: 85% likelihood of finishing within predicted time range."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "7. Is there audio coaching during runs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Premium+ users access real-time audio cues via smartphone: pace alerts, cadence reminders, heart rate zone guidance, and motivational prompts. Audio coaching integrates with Spotify/Apple Music (playlist auto-adjusts to cadence). Pro plans include AI-generated adaptive coaching that responds to fatigue signals mid-run. Offline audio packs available for areas with poor connectivity. 15+ voice options including celebrity cameos (Elite plan)."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "8. Can I share my plan with a coach or running group?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, collaboration features include: plan sharing via link (view-only or edit access), export to PDF/Google Sheets, integration with TrainingPeaks and Final Surge, and group training plans (Elite plan) where coaches manage multiple athletes. Running clubs can create shared plans with group long runs. Real-time plan updates sync to all collaborators within 60 seconds."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "9. What support is available if I have questions?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Free users access knowledge base and community forum. Premium users receive email support within 72 hours. Pro users get priority email (24-hour) and live chat. Elite users receive 1-on-1 video calls with certified running coaches (monthly) and unlimited messaging. Support covers plan adjustments, injury prevention advice, race strategy, and gear recommendations. Coach certifications: USATF, RRCA, or equivalent."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "10. How do I cancel or get a refund?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cancel anytime in account settings. Refund policy: 30-day money-back guarantee for annual plans. Monthly plans can be cancelled without penalty but no prorated refund. Elite plan coaching sessions are non-refundable once delivered. Upon cancellation, export your plan history and race results. Data retained for 90 days if you reactivate. Delete account via privacy@runningtrainingplan.com. ---"
      }
    }
  ]
}
    </script>
    
